														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4728604">
									

<p>this was a slog to read, and it just isn't as good as the forum-style entries on the site. i get excited every time i see that parawatch header. but the style of this article comes off more as the World's Most Boring Amateur Wiki article. and the fake footnotes &#8212; though i do understand the stylistic choice &#8212; make it even tougher to get through.</p>
<p>the final nail is the big black statement from the primary character, which is absolutely impossible to get through. it's not interesting, it reads like bad prose, and it gets downright nonsensical (and not in a fun or scary way) at times.</p>
<p>-1. i appreciate what you tried to do here, bringing parawatch back to its roots, but this one is a miss for me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
